# Tauri Rust Backend Conventions

- Keep native responsibilities in Rust: global hotkeys, DWM thumbnails, native window lifecycle, focus tracking, and process scanning.
- Expose small, typed Tauri command surfaces; validate all inputs at command boundaries.
- Organize backend by domain modules: `db`, `hotkeys`, `thumbnail_service`, `windows`, `dwm`, `eve_profile_tools`.
- Use explicit error types (`thiserror` or equivalent) and return actionable error messages to frontend.
- Avoid blocking the UI thread/event loop; use async tasks and coordinated shared state (`Arc<Mutex<_>>`/channels) carefully.
- Persist runtime settings in SQLite and keep schema changes additive with migrations.
- Add concise safety comments around Win32 interop and `unsafe` blocks; keep `unsafe` scopes minimal.
